TITLE: Creating an Axios Instance
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to create a new instance of Axios with a custom configuration.  It sets the `baseURL`, `timeout`, and custom headers for the instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const instance = axios.create({
  baseURL: 'https://some-domain.com/api/',
  timeout: 1000,
  headers: {'X-Custom-Header': 'foobar'}
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Posting Form Data using form-data Library (Node.js)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to send form data, including files and buffers, using the `form-data` library in Node.js. It also shows how to set the correct headers for the request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_32

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const FormData = require('form-data');

const form = new FormData();
form.append('my_field', 'my value');
form.append('my_buffer', new Buffer(10));
form.append('my_file', fs.createReadStream('/foo/bar.jpg'));

axios.post('https://example.com', form, { headers: form.getHeaders() })
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Making Requests with Axios Config
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to make a POST request using Axios with a configuration object. It specifies the method, URL, and data to be sent.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Send a POST request
axios({
  method: 'post',
  url: '/user/12345',
  data: {
    firstName: 'Fred',
    lastName: 'Flintstone'
  }
});
```

