TITLE: Following Redirects with http.get in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the `follow-redirects` module to make an HTTP GET request that automatically follows redirects.  It imports the `http` and `https` objects from the `follow-redirects` module and uses `http.get` to retrieve data from a URL that redirects. The response data is then logged to the console. The error handler catches any request errors. Dependencies: follow-redirects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/follow-redirects/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { http, https } = require('follow-redirects');

http.get('http://bit.ly/900913', response => {
  response.on('data', chunk => {
    console.log(chunk);
  });
}).on('error', err => {
  console.error(err);
});
```

