TITLE: Submitting Form with Custom Headers
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to submit form data with custom HTTP headers.  The `headers` key is used within the object passed to `form.submit()` to define the custom headers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/form-data/Readme.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
form.submit({
  host: 'example.com',
  path: '/surelynot.php',
  headers: {'x-test-header': 'test-header-value'}
}, function(err, res) {
  console.log(res.statusCode);
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Performing Concurrent Requests with Axios
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to perform multiple concurrent requests using Axios and `Promise.all`.  It fetches user account and permissions data concurrently and processes the results when all requests are complete.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function getUserAccount() {
  return axios.get('/user/12345');
}

function getUserPermissions() {
  return axios.get('/user/12345/permissions');
}

Promise.all([getUserAccount(), getUserPermissions()])
  .then(function (results) {
    const acct = results[0];
    const perm = results[1];
  });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Posting Form Data using URLSearchParams (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to send data in the `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` format in a browser environment using the `URLSearchParams` API.  Dependencies: URLSearchParams API (polyfill required for older browsers)
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_27

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const params = new URLSearchParams();
params.append('param1', 'value1');
params.append('param2', 'value2');
axios.post('/foo', params);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Posting Form Data using qs Library and ES6 (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates an alternative approach to using the `qs` library for serializing data with ES6 syntax, including setting headers for the correct content type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import qs from 'qs';
const data = { 'bar': 123 };
const options = {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'content-type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },
  data: qs.stringify(data),
  url,
};
axios(options);
```

