TITLE: Webpack Configuration for follow-redirects Browser Usage
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure webpack to replace `follow-redirects` with the built-in browser equivalents (`http` and `https`) when using `follow-redirects` in a browser environment.  This optimizes the bundle size and uses the browser's native redirect handling.  Requires: webpack
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/follow-redirects/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "follow-redirects/http"  : "http",
  "follow-redirects/https" : "https"
}
```

