TITLE: Submitting Form to URL with Query String and Auth
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to submit a form to a URL containing a query string and HTTP authentication credentials. The parameters are passed as an object to the form.submit() method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/form-data/Readme.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
form.submit({
  host: 'example.com',
  path: '/probably.php?extra=params',
  auth: 'username:password'
}, function(err, res) {
  console.log(res.statusCode);
});
```

