TITLE: Creating Form with String, Buffer, and File Stream
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to construct a form with three fields containing a string, a buffer, and a file stream using the form-data library. It showcases appending different types of data to the form.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/form-data/Readme.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var FormData = require('form-data');
var fs = require('fs');

var form = new FormData();
form.append('my_field', 'my value');
form.append('my_buffer', new Buffer(10));
form.append('my_file', fs.createReadStream('/foo/bar.jpg'));
```

