TITLE: Canceling Axios Requests with Executor Function (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates an alternative way to cancel Axios requests using the `CancelToken` constructor with an executor function. This allows you to obtain a cancel function that can be called later.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sumsubstance/apptokenusageexamples/blob/master/JS/node_modules/axios/README.md#_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const CancelToken = axios.CancelToken;
let cancel;

axios.get('/user/12345', {
  cancelToken: new CancelToken(function executor(c) {
    // An executor function receives a cancel function as a parameter
    cancel = c;
  })
});

// cancel the request
cancel();
```

